Class IssueSubmitTask

java.lang.Object
  org.apache.tools.ant.ProjectComponent

              org.mantisbt.connect.ant.taskdefs.IssueSubmitTask
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
public class IssueSubmitTask
extends MantisConnectTask

This task can be used to submit issues via Ant.

The following attributes are mandatory:

  • url
  • username
  • password
  • project (The name of the project)
  • summary
  • description

The following attributes are optional:

  • proxHost (Mandatory if proxyPort is given)
  • proxyPort (Mandatory if proxyHost is given)
  • category
  • version
  • reproducibility
  • severity
  • priority
  • additionalInfo
  • stepsToReproduce
  • private
  • platform
  • os
  • osVersion
  • productBuild
  • failOnError (Indicates whether the build should fail if an error occures - defaults to true)
  • sessionClass: Classname for the Session to use. The class must implement org.mantisbt.connect.IMCSession and provide a public constructor with the following arguments:
    1. java.net.URL - URL
    2. java.lang.String - username
    3. java.lang.String - password
    4. java.lang.String - proxyHost
    5. int - proxyPort
    This attribute ist optional.

Enumerations (reproducibility, severity and priority):

For each enumeration you can use strings. The strings map to integers as defined for the appropriate enum in config_defaults_inc.php of Mantis. If you've defined your own enums then you can use integers instead of strings.

  • reproducibility: "always" (10), "sometimes" (30), "random" (50), "have-not-tried" (70), "unable-to-reproduce" (90), "n/a" (100)
  • severity: "feature" (10), "trivial" (20), "text" (30), "tweak" (40), "minor" (50), "major" (60), "crash" (70), "block" (80)
  • priority: "none" (10), "low" (20), "normal" (30), "high" (40), "urgent" (50), "immediate" (60)

Support for custom fields:

Custom fields can be added by nesting customfield elements within a submit task.

The attributes name and value are mandatory for customfield elements.

Remarks:

  • Use "true" or "false" for custom fields of type Checkboxfield.
  • If a custom field is of type Date then a third attribute format is mandatory which defines the format of the given date.

Example:

In the following example all attributes and two custom fields are set. The first custom field would be a string the second one would be a date. Note that instead of using sometimes, block and high for reproducibility, severity and priority you could also use the integer values 30, 80 and 40. 

       <taskdef name="submitissue" classname="org.mantisbt.connect.ant.taskdefs.IssueSubmitTask" classpath="${cp}" />
       
       <target name="submit-issue">
                <submitissue url="http://yourhost/mantis/mc/mantisconnect.php"
                        username="AUser"
                        password="APassword"
                        project="AProjectName"
                        category="ACategory"
                        summary="ASummary"
                        description="ADescription"
                        version="AVersion"
                        reproducibility="sometimes"
                        severity="block"
                        priority="high"
                        additionalInfo="AdditionalInfo"
                        platform="APlatform"
                        os="AnOs"
                        osVersion="AnOsVersion"
                        productBuild="AProductBuild"
                        stepsToReproduce="StepsToReproduce"
                        private="true&quot
                        failOnError="false">
                        <customfield name="AStringField" value="AValue"/>
                        <customfield name="ADateField" value="01.01.2000" format="dd.MM.yy"/>
                </submit>
       </target>
